@startuml object-diagram
title Stock Guard - Object Diagram (illustrative snapshot after one usage log)
skinparam objectAttributeIconSize 0

object "<u>currentUser</u> : User" as u {
  email = "ops@example.com"
  role = "Operational Staff"
  status = "Active"
}

object "<u>gloves</u> : Inventory" as i {
  itemName = "Nitrile Gloves"
  currentStock = 18
  reorderThreshold = 8
  totalUsed = 24
  riskLevel = "Low"
}

object "<u>log_2026_01_20</u> : UsageLog" as l {
  itemId = "ObjectId( ... gloves._id )"
  itemName = "Nitrile Gloves"
  quantityUsed = 2
  usageDate = "2026-01-20"
  remainingStock = 18
  riskLevel = "Low"
}

l -down-> i : itemId

object "<u>appSettings</u> : SystemSettings" as s {
  systemName = "StockGuard System"
  lowStockThreshold = 10
  darkMode = false
}

note right of l
  itemId in MongoDB stores the
  same ObjectId as gloves._id.
  usageDate is a YYYY-MM-DD string.
end note
note bottom of s
  Typically one document;
  not linked by FK to User/Inventory.
end note
note right of u
  Session holds identity;
  not a DB FK in other collections
  in Release 1.0.
end note

@enduml
